free_txt: Preliminary data on 197Au
Experiment performed at WNR
spallation neutron source on the 60R (60deg right)
flight path using GEANIE spectrometer
Compiled by S.H.
Reference to Nice 2007 conference included
SD: REACTION code corrected in Subents 2-16
By N.Fotiades (2012-08-23): All transition-cross
sections reported in Phys.Rev.C80(2009)044612 are all
corrected for internal conversion using the values
in Table 1 of the article.
Spectrometer GEANIE consisting of 11 Compton
suppressed planar Ge detectors (low-energy photon
spectrometer LEPS), nine Compton suppressed coaxial
Ge detectors, and six unsuppressed coaxial Ge
detectors.
The neutron flux on target was measured with
a fission chamber, consisting of 235U and 238U
foils, located 18.5m from the center of the
spallation target.
Total uncertainty
Systematic uncertainty in sample thickness
Systematic uncertainty in Fe foil thickness
Systematic uncertainty in detector efficiency
Systematic uncertainty in gamma ray absorption
Systematic uncertainty in gamma ray
internal conversion
Systematic uncertainty in neutron flux
Experiment performed at WNR
spallation neutron source on the 60R (60deg right)
flight path using GEANIE spectrometer
The neutrons were produced in a natural W
spallation target driven by an 800 MeV proton beam
Energy of incident neutrons determined by time
of flight technique. Proton beam time structure
consisted of 625 mu-s long macropulses, each
macropulse containing sub-nanosecond-wide micropulses,
spaced every 1.8 mu-s(197Au experiment) or
3.6 mu-s(191Ir and 193Ir experiments).
Gamma ray production cross sections
determined by gamma ray spectrometry
strong 846.8 keV,
2+ - 0+ transition of 56Fe, produced in natural Fe
from inelastic scattering was used to normalize the
cross sections

capsule, 2.3 cm in diameter, containing 2.0 g of Ir

foils were placed on the front of the targets
during part of the experiments for normalization.
